article.headline: Nicholls State 39, McNeese State 26
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. (AP) -- Nicholls State clinched the 2005 Southland Conference Championship Saturday on the strength of its running game in a 39-26 win over McNeese State. The Colonels (6-3, 5-1 Southland) amassed 458 yards on the ground. Quarterback Yale Vannoy threw for just 12 yards, but piled up 102 yards rushing, second only to Anthony Harris' 149 yards on 18 carries. Harris also had a 3-yard TD run in the fourth. Cole Broderick finished the night with a total of 68 yards rushing, including three touchdowns. Chris Jones was 9-for-19 and 194 yards for the Cowboys (5-4, 3-3). Quint Lawrence had seven catches for 199 yards, including two touchdowns -- a 54-yard pass from Carlo Franklin in the first and a 46-yard pass from Jones in the fourth. Blake Bercegeay also kicked two field goals for the Cowboys, one from 33 yards out and another from 28.
